
<section id="MidiConvert">
  <title>Converters</title>

  <para>
    The following opcodes can convert MIDI information from a MIDI-triggered instrument instance:
    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          MIDI note number to frequency converters: <link linkend="cpsmidi"><citetitle>cpsmidi</citetitle></link>, <link linkend="cpsmidib"><citetitle>cpsmidib</citetitle></link>, <link linkend="cpstmid"><citetitle>cpstmid</citetitle></link>, <link linkend="octmidi"><citetitle>octmidi</citetitle></link>, <link linkend="octmidib"><citetitle>octmidib</citetitle></link>, <link linkend="pchmidi"><citetitle>pchmidi</citetitle></link> and <link linkend="pchmidib"><citetitle>pchmidib</citetitle></link>.
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Pitch/frequency to MIDI note number converters: <link
          linkend="ftom"><citetitle>ftom</citetitle></link>, <link
          linkend="pchtom"><citetitle>pchtome</citetitle></link>.
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
        MIDI velocity to amplitude converters: <link linkend="ampmidi"><citetitle>ampmidi</citetitle></link> and <link linkend="ampmidid"><citetitle>ampmidid</citetitle></link>.
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
  </para>

</section>
